A20. Participate in a Discussion about a Cybersecurity Event

In our discussion, we focused on the hacking group ShinyHunters and their high-profile attack on Ticketmaster. During this incident, approximately 1.3 terabytes of user data were stolen, including names, email addresses, phone numbers, home addresses, ticket purchase history, and partial credit card information. The stolen data was subsequently sold on the dark web.
Given the scale of the breach, users are at significant risk of identity theft, phishing attacks, and financial fraud. While the exact financial loss to Ticketmaster remains unclear, lawsuits and mitigation costs indicate that the company likely incurred substantial expenses.
Our discussion primarily centered on the potential attacks by ShinyHunters that might go undetected by the company. We also explored various techniques used by the group to compromise systems and considered the possibility of additional attack types that may have occurred but were not publicly recorded.
Overall, this discussion highlighted the importance of proactive cybersecurity measures, continuous monitoring, and user awareness to mitigate the risks associated with large-scale data breaches.
